oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The memorial on the State Capital Grounds to the three Governors of Tennessee named Brown. Side shown honors Neill S. Brown, governor from 1847 to 1849.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Brown also served as a member of the state legislature for six years, minister to Russia, and a delegate to the Constitutional Convention of 1870.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Monuments & memorials
